00:28:16,612 --> 00:28:18,655
Yeah. I have to wake up.

247
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:22,242
Wake up. Wake up. Wake up.

248
00:28:22,492 --> 00:28:24,661
Wake up!

249
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:43,722
Kid!

250
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:46,099
Kid, get your head out of the clouds!

251
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:47,809
Wake up, kid!

252
00:28:47,976 --> 00:28:51,772
There's no sleepwalking
on the Polar Express.

253
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:54,608
We gotta jump them knuckles.

254
00:28:57,319 --> 00:28:59,279
Come on, kid. Flip my shoulders.

255
00:28:59,446 --> 00:29:01,281
Grab my lily.

256
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:06,411
That skirt you're chasing
must have moved ahead.

257
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:10,999
- We gotta hightail it to the hog, pronto.
-To the hog?

258
00:29:11,833 --> 00:29:15,170
The engine. The engine, you tenderfoot.

259
00:29:15,337 --> 00:29:18,548
We gotta make the engine
before we hit Flat Top Tunnel.

260
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:20,384
How come?

261
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:23,178
So many questions.

262
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:27,933
There is but one inch of clearance
between the roof of this rattler...

263
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,978
...and the roof of Flat Top Tunnel.

264
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:33,021
Savvy?

265
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:39,194
It's just the run up to the hump, kid.

266
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:41,697
This will be interesting.

267
00:30:04,886 --> 00:30:06,596
Get back on, kid. Hurry!

268
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:09,057
Grab my muck stick.

269
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:47,262
There's only one trick to this, kid.

270
00:30:48,430 --> 00:30:49,931
When I say "jump"...

271
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:56,271
...you jump!

272
00:31:19,086 --> 00:31:22,255
You. I thought you got thrown off, and--

273
00:31:22,631 --> 00:31:25,467
- You're driving the train?
-They put me in charge.

274
00:31:25,634 --> 00:31:29,054
- The engineer had to check the light.
-Here's the light. Careful.

275
00:31:29,221 --> 00:31:30,889
All right, now.

276
00:31:33,016 --> 00:31:34,518
I got it.

277
00:31:37,229 --> 00:31:40,732
- How do you know how'?
-it's easy. Come here, I'll show you.

278
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:43,360
This big lever here, that's the throttle.

279
00:31:43,527 --> 00:31:45,654
This little one here, that's the brake.

280
00:31:45,821 --> 00:31:48,698
And those are the pressure gauges.

281
00:31:48,865 --> 00:31:51,451
And that rope is the whistle.

282
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:53,829
The whistle.

283
00:31:54,621 --> 00:31:56,540
You wanna try it?

284
00:31:59,376 --> 00:32:02,379
I've wanted to do that my whole life.

285
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:09,094
Hold still! Hold still! Don't move!

286
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:11,304
Look!

287
00:32:23,525 --> 00:32:26,987
Stop the train! Stop the train!

288
00:32:28,029 --> 00:32:29,865
Stop the train!

289
00:32:32,826 --> 00:32:34,536
What?

290
00:32:34,703 --> 00:32:37,372
They want us to stop the train.

291
00:32:37,539 --> 00:32:40,000
- Which one is the brake?
-He told me this was.

292
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:41,877
- Who?
-The engineer.

293
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:46,673
- The engineer? This one looks like a brake.
-No, he said this was the brake.

294
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:47,883
Are you sure?

295
00:32:49,384 --> 00:32:50,677
Are you sure?

296
00:32:57,767 --> 00:33:00,479
Pull the brake!

297
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:02,564
Stop the train!

298
00:33:19,915 --> 00:33:21,875
Caribou?

299
00:33:24,419 --> 00:33:28,298
There can be no Christmas without
the Polar Express arriving on time.

300
00:33:28,465 --> 00:33:31,760
Am I the only one who understands that?

301
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:34,721
You. I should have known.

302
00:33:34,888 --> 00:33:38,767
Are you bound and determined that
this train never reaches the North Pole?

303
00:33:38,934 --> 00:33:40,519
But look.

304
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:43,438
Caribou crossing?!

305
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:48,026
I make that herd to be at least
100,000, maybe even a million.

306
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:51,279
It's gonna be hours
before they clear this track.

307
00:33:51,446 --> 00:33:55,492
- A tough nut to crack.
-We are in some serious jelly.

308
00:33:55,659 --> 00:33:58,119
- And a jam.
-Tight spot.

309
00:33:58,286 --> 00:33:59,621
- Up a creek.
-Up a tree.

310
00:33:59,788 --> 00:34:02,999
- Lost in the grass.
<i>- I'll</i> tell you what's grass: our a--

311
00:34:45,417 --> 00:34:49,838
Problem solved. All ahead, slow.

312
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,719
We're going pretty fast.

313
00:35:37,886 --> 00:35:40,764
Tell the engineer to slow down.

314
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:47,729
Slow it down.

315
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:52,359
Watch the speed!

316
00:35:57,405 --> 00:36:00,450
Jumping jeepers,
the cotter pin sheared off.

317
00:36:00,617 --> 00:36:01,910
- What?
-The pin.

318
00:36:02,077 --> 00:36:04,245
- Where?
-There.

319
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:05,955
- Oh, no.
-Oh, no.

320
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:09,918
- They can't hear me.
-They can't?

321
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:15,840
I don't like the look of this.
Under the safety bar.

322
00:36:18,218 --> 00:36:19,886
Is everything all right?
What should we do?

323
00:36:20,053 --> 00:36:24,516
Considering we've lost communication
with the engineer...

324
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:27,852
...we are standing totally exposed
on the front of the locomotive...

325
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:31,189
...the train appears to be
accelerating uncontrollably...

326
00:36:31,356 --> 00:36:35,193
...and we are rapidly
approaching Glacier Gulch...

327
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:38,863
...which happens to be the steepest
downhill grade in the world...

328
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:42,325
...I suggest we all hold on...

329
00:36:42,867 --> 00:36:45,120
...tigh'ily-

330
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:07,142
- The pin.
-The pin.

331
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:30,540
Jiminy Christmas, the ice has frozen
over the tracks.

332
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:55,106
Hold on. Hold on. No, no.

333
00:37:56,024 --> 00:37:58,151
Come on. Watch your step.

334
00:37:58,318 --> 00:38:01,529
Come on, sweetie.
Up you go. Up you go.

335
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:06,451
Put your feet on here. On here.

336
00:38:08,995 --> 00:38:10,288
Little adventure, huh?

337
00:38:10,455 --> 00:38:12,874
Young man, quick thinking on your part.

338
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:36,731
Step to your left, please. To your left.

339
00:38:40,568 --> 00:38:44,072
Well, that is more like it.

340
00:38:46,449 --> 00:38:49,160
What in the name of Mike?

341
00:38:52,288 --> 00:38:53,748
Look.

342
00:38:56,376 --> 00:38:59,128
Get us the blazes out of here!

343
00:39:07,387 --> 00:39:08,972
Turn this sled around.

344
00:39:27,448 --> 00:39:28,867
Look there.

345
00:39:31,578 --> 00:39:32,912
Tracks.

346
00:39:33,079 --> 00:39:34,497
Dead ahead.

347
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:41,462
Right.

348
00:39:47,302 --> 00:39:48,303
Left.

349
00:39:53,808 --> 00:39:54,809
Right.

350
00:39:58,688 --> 00:39:59,939
Hang a Louie.

351
00:40:03,067 --> 00:40:04,444
Toss a Ritchie.

352
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:09,490
Port astern.

353
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:13,494
To the starboard.

354
00:40:14,787 --> 00:40:17,373
- My slipper.
-You're gonna lose your ticket.

355
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:19,417
It's not my ticket, it's yours.

356
00:40:19,584 --> 00:40:21,419
-It's my ticket?
-Yes.

357
00:40:21,586 --> 00:40:23,713
Right. Keep up with me. Left.

358
00:40:24,047 --> 00:40:26,466
Right. Left.

359
00:40:30,511 --> 00:40:31,846
Right.

360
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:33,473
Left.

361
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,016
Right.

362
00:40:35,183 --> 00:40:37,143
Left. Right.

363
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:42,148
- Oh, no!
-Oh, no!

364
00:40:44,359 --> 00:40:46,194
Brace yourselves!

365
00:40:57,246 --> 00:40:59,165
Well, that's more like it.

366
00:41:01,542 --> 00:41:03,086
Thank you.

367
00:41:03,252 --> 00:41:06,547
Thank you. I can't believe
you found my ticket.

368
00:41:07,090 --> 00:41:09,717
Did someone say they found a ticket?

369
00:41:11,719 --> 00:41:15,139
Well, in that case... Tickets, please.

370
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:25,566
Thank you.

371
00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:31,197
_IIL_EII?
-Just like that know-it-all kid.

372
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:48,715
Watch your step.
Tricky walking up here.

373
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:51,259
It's mighty slick.
Mighty slick, I tell you.

374
00:41:52,427 --> 00:41:54,971
There you go. What did I tell you?

375
00:41:55,138 --> 00:42:00,268
Years ago, on my first Christmas Eve run,
I was up on the roof making my rounds...

376
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:02,353
...when I slipped on the ice myself.

377
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:05,940
I reached out for a hand iron,
but it broke off. I slid and fell.

378
00:42:06,107 --> 00:42:10,111
And yet, I did not fall off this train.

379
00:42:10,695 --> 00:42:12,947
Someone saved you?

380
00:42:13,114 --> 00:42:15,116
Or something.

381
00:42:17,994 --> 00:42:19,287
An angel.

382
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:21,873
Maybe.

383
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,125
Wait. Wait.

384
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:28,129
What did he look like? Did you see him?

385
00:42:29,255 --> 00:42:33,134
No, sir. But sometimes
seeing is believing.

386
00:42:33,509 --> 00:42:38,639
And sometimes the most real things
in the world are the things we can't see.

387
00:42:44,479 --> 00:42:46,814
The forsaken and the abandoned.

388
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:51,986
Mind your step, now.
These poor toys have suffered enough...

389
00:42:52,153 --> 00:42:56,491
...being left to rust and decay in the
back alleys and vacant lots of the world.

390
00:42:56,991 --> 00:43:01,162
- What are they doing here?
-it's a new concept the boss came up with.

391
00:43:01,329 --> 00:43:04,707
Instead of being thrown away,
they're collected. Refurbished.

392
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:10,505
He calls it "rebicycling."
Something like that.

393
00:43:12,757 --> 00:43:15,176
Makes me wanna cry...

394
00:43:15,343 --> 00:43:18,513
...seeing toys that were
treated this way.

395
00:43:19,305 --> 00:43:23,518
These hopelessly entangled
string puppets and marionettes...

396
00:43:23,684 --> 00:43:27,980
...pose a particular problem. We found
the nimble fingers of our work force...

397
00:43:28,147 --> 00:43:32,485
...here at the North Pole are best
for working out those knots and tangles.

398
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:35,196
Thank you. Double-locked here.

399
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:50,044
You are just like me, my friend.

400
00:43:50,211 --> 00:43:52,588
A scrooge!

401
00:43:52,755 --> 00:43:54,924
Ebenezer Scrooge.

402
00:43:55,091 --> 00:43:58,427
North Pole, Santa Claus, this train...

403
00:43:58,594 --> 00:44:02,515
...it's all a bunch of humbug.
A bout of indigestion.

404
00:44:02,682 --> 00:44:05,268
Oh, yeah. I know what you are.

405
00:44:05,434 --> 00:44:08,062
You're a doubter.

406
00:44:08,229 --> 00:44:10,773
A doubter. You don't believe!

407
00:44:10,940 --> 00:44:14,110
You're a doubter! You don't believe!

408
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:34,130
You missed it.
We rode down some really sharp hills.

409
00:44:34,297 --> 00:44:38,676
We were on what looked like a frozen lake.
But I know it was just an optical illusion.

410
00:44:38,843 --> 00:44:41,762
He said the train was on ice.
I said it's impossible--

411
00:44:41,929 --> 00:44:44,640
You can't put a train track--
Where you going now?

412
00:44:59,155 --> 00:45:02,116
<i>I'm wishing on a star</i>

413
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:05,453
<i>And trying to believe</i>

414
00:45:05,620 --> 00:45:08,789
<i>That even though it's far</i>

415
00:45:09,248 --> 00:45:11,792
<i>He'll find me Christmas Eve</i>

416
00:45:12,418 --> 00:45:15,546
<i>I guess that Santa's busy</i>

417
00:45:15,713 --> 00:45:18,716
<i>'Cause he's never come around</i>

418
00:45:19,217 --> 00:45:24,972
<i>I think of him
When Christmas comes to town</i>

419
00:45:25,765 --> 00:45:28,935
<i>The best time of the year</i>

420
00:45:29,101 --> 00:45:32,313
<i>When everyone comes home</i>

421
00:45:32,480 --> 00:45:35,650
<i>With all this Christmas cheer</i>

422
00:45:35,816 --> 00:45:39,362
<i>It's hard to be alone</i>

423
00:45:39,528 --> 00:45:45,576
<i>Putting up the Christmas tree
With friends who come around</i>

424
00:45:45,743 --> 00:45:52,124
<i>It's so much fun
When Christmas comes to town</i>

425
00:45:52,917 --> 00:45:59,006
<i>Presents for the children
Wrapped in red and green</i>

426
00:45:59,548 --> 00:46:05,346
<i>All the things I've heard about
But never really seen</i>

427
00:46:06,180 --> 00:46:08,683
<i>No one will be sleeping</i>

428
00:46:08,849 --> 00:46:11,936
<i>On the night of Christmas Eve</i>

429
00:46:12,103 --> 00:46:19,193
<i>Hoping Santa's on his way</i>

430
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:22,446
<i>When Santa's sleighbells ring</i>

431
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:25,491
<i>I listen all around</i>

432
00:46:25,658 --> 00:46:28,869
<i>The herald angels sing</i>

433
00:46:29,036 --> 00:46:32,039
<i>I never hear a sound</i>

434
00:46:32,581 --> 00:46:36,043
<i>And all the dreams of children</i>

435
00:46:36,210 --> 00:46:39,005
<i>Once lost will all be found</i>

436
00:46:39,171 --> 00:46:45,094
<i>That's all I want
When Christmas comes to town</i>

437
00:46:47,471 --> 00:46:56,147
<i>That's all I want
When Christmas comes to town</i>

438
00:47:07,658 --> 00:47:09,118
Look.

439
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:13,789
The northern lights.

440
00:47:16,625 --> 00:47:18,669
Hey. You three.

441
00:47:19,879 --> 00:47:21,672
We just crossed it.

442
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:27,261
Latitude 66°33'.
The Arctic Circle.

443
00:47:27,428 --> 00:47:30,765
And do you see?
Those lights in the distance.

444
00:47:31,682 --> 00:47:36,145
They look like the lights of a strange
ocean liner sailing on a frozen sea.

445
00:47:37,438 --> 00:47:39,440
There...

446
00:47:40,107 --> 00:47:42,151
...is the North Pole.

447
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:49,992
<i>It's a magic carpet on a rail
It never takes a rest</i>

448
00:47:50,159 --> 00:47:53,329
<i>Flying through
The mountains and the snow</i>

449
00:47:53,496 --> 00:47:56,457
<i>You can ride for free and join the fun
If you just say yes</i>

450
00:47:56,624 --> 00:47:59,960
<i>'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express</i>

451
00:48:00,127 --> 00:48:03,255
<i>Whoo, Whoo, the whistle blows
That's the sound of her singing</i>

452
00:48:03,422 --> 00:48:06,634
<i>Ding, ding, the bell will ring
Golly, look at her go</i>

453
00:48:06,801 --> 00:48:09,804
<i>You wonder if you'll get there soon
Anybody's guess</i>

454
00:48:09,970 --> 00:48:13,182
<i>'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express</i>

455
00:48:13,349 --> 00:48:16,477
<i>When we get there
We'll scream, "Yay!"</i>

456
00:48:16,644 --> 00:48:18,979
<i>We'll arrive with
A bang, bang, bang</i>

457
00:48:19,146 --> 00:48:22,149
<i>Boom, boom, boom
Laughing all the way</i>

458
00:48:27,154 --> 00:48:30,074
We made it. With five minutes to spare.

459
00:48:30,241 --> 00:48:32,118
We made it.

460
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,854
There should be elves.
Where are the elves?

461
00:49:00,020 --> 00:49:01,689
Yeah, where are the elves?

462
00:49:01,856 --> 00:49:04,191
They are gathering
in the center of the city.

463
00:49:04,358 --> 00:49:08,154
That is where Santa will give
the first gift of Christmas.

464
00:49:09,029 --> 00:49:11,490
Who gets the first gift of Christmas?

465
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:15,536
He will choose one of you.

466
00:49:18,747 --> 00:49:21,542
- Look.
-Elves!

467
00:49:52,406 --> 00:49:54,742
All right. All right,
ladies and gentlemen.

468
00:49:54,909 --> 00:49:57,620
Two columns, if you please.

469
00:49:57,786 --> 00:50:00,581
Shorter in the front, taller in the rear.

470
00:50:01,081 --> 00:50:04,710
Even-numbered birthdays on the right,
odd-numbered on the left.

471
00:50:04,877 --> 00:50:07,796
No pushing. No pushing.
But let's not dilly-dally.

472
00:50:07,963 --> 00:50:09,882
It's five minutes to midnight.

473
00:50:10,049 --> 00:50:13,636
Hey, what gives? It was five minutes
till midnight four minutes ago.

474
00:50:14,094 --> 00:50:16,597
Exactly. Columns of two.

475
00:50:16,764 --> 00:50:18,891
- One, two.
-Excuse me.

476
00:50:19,058 --> 00:50:21,519
- Question.
-What about him?

477
00:50:24,271 --> 00:50:26,982
No one is required to see Santa.

478
00:50:28,108 --> 00:50:31,320
Ladies and gentlemen,
you do not have to hold hands...

479
00:50:31,487 --> 00:50:34,949
- Come on.
-...but please remain in your columns...

480
00:50:35,115 --> 00:50:37,493
...while we are in transit.

481
00:50:47,127 --> 00:50:50,631
- Look, you have to come with us.
-She's right.

482
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:57,012
Christmas just doesn't work out
for me. Never has.

483
00:50:57,179 --> 00:50:59,807
But Christmas is such a wonderful,
beautiful time.

484
00:50:59,974 --> 00:51:03,602
It's a time for giving and being thankful,
for friends and family.

485
00:51:03,769 --> 00:51:08,566
People hang decorations and lights. Santa
leaves presents under our Christmas trees.

486
00:51:10,484 --> 00:51:12,236
Christmas just...

487
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:14,697
...doesn't work out for me.

488
00:51:16,490 --> 00:51:20,202
Look, I don't know if Christmas
is gonna work out for you or not...

489
00:51:20,369 --> 00:51:23,497
...but this is Christmas Eve.
Don't stay here by yourself.

490
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:26,709
Yes, come with us.

491
00:51:27,251 --> 00:51:29,044
We'll go together.

492
00:51:41,140 --> 00:51:42,766
Oh, no.

493
00:51:50,816 --> 00:51:52,693
We're gonna be okay.

