01:24:46,164 --> 01:24:47,457
Look.

756
01:24:50,127 --> 01:24:53,005
Santa got to Billy's house already.

757
01:24:55,799 --> 01:24:58,552
Look, look! Santa got here!

758
01:24:58,719 --> 01:25:00,304
Isn't that amazing?

759
01:25:00,470 --> 01:25:01,888
It is amazing.

760
01:25:09,271 --> 01:25:11,398
It is amazing.

761
01:25:57,736 --> 01:26:00,030
I'm sorry about the bell.

762
01:26:00,614 --> 01:26:03,283
It was a really special present.

763
01:26:03,450 --> 01:26:05,202
Well, you know what they say.

764
01:26:05,369 --> 01:26:07,663
It's the thought that counts.

765
01:26:08,330 --> 01:26:09,790
Yeah.

766
01:26:10,957 --> 01:26:13,835
Well, see you.

767
01:26:16,421 --> 01:26:17,964
Well...

768
01:26:18,590 --> 01:26:20,217
...see you.

769
01:26:21,093 --> 01:26:22,594
See you.

770
01:26:36,400 --> 01:26:38,902
Watch your step, please.

771
01:26:40,153 --> 01:26:41,405
Thank you.

772
01:26:41,571 --> 01:26:44,116
No, thank you.

773
01:26:45,867 --> 01:26:47,661
One thing about trains:

774
01:26:47,828 --> 01:26:49,913
It doesn't matter where they're going.

775
01:26:50,080 --> 01:26:54,126
What matters is deciding to get on.

776
01:27:11,101 --> 01:27:12,602
Merry Christmas!

777
01:27:16,314 --> 01:27:17,524
What?

778
01:27:18,650 --> 01:27:23,196
Merry Christmas!

779
01:28:31,723 --> 01:28:36,102
Wake up. Wake up.
Santa's been here. Santa's been here.

780
01:28:36,269 --> 01:28:37,938
Hurry up. Hurry up!

781
01:28:38,104 --> 01:28:41,441
Mom, Dad, wake up. Wake up!

782
01:28:41,608 --> 01:28:44,611
Santa's been here! Santa's been here!

783
01:28:44,778 --> 01:28:48,698
Mom, Dad, look!
He brought us all kinds of stuff!

784
01:28:48,865 --> 01:28:51,409
Look, a train!

785
01:29:07,801 --> 01:29:13,306
This is the beautiful-est,
most wonderful-est Christmas ever.

786
01:29:13,473 --> 01:29:15,767
Wait. Look.

787
01:29:17,060 --> 01:29:18,937
Here's one more.

788
01:29:20,480 --> 01:29:22,357
Has your name on it.

789
01:29:51,344 --> 01:29:53,847
<i>Found this on the seat of my sleigh.</i>

790
01:29:54,014 --> 01:29:56,683
<i>Better fix that hole in your pocket.</i>

791
01:29:56,850 --> 01:29:58,101
<i>Mr. C.</i>

792
01:30:08,153 --> 01:30:11,323
Oh, what a beautiful bell.
Who's it from?

793
01:30:11,489 --> 01:30:13,533
- Santa.
-Santa?

794
01:30:13,700 --> 01:30:15,327
Really?

795
01:30:16,369 --> 01:30:18,788
- Oh, that's too bad.
-What's this?

796
01:30:19,831 --> 01:30:21,333
Broken.

797
01:30:22,459 --> 01:30:24,628
Sorry about that, sport.

798
01:30:29,174 --> 01:30:32,302
Come on, kids. We don't wanna be late.

799
01:30:40,352 --> 01:30:43,855
<i>At one time, most of my friends
could hear the bell.</i>

800
01:30:44,022 --> 01:30:48,068
<i>But as years passed,
it fell silent for all of them.</i>

801
01:30:48,234 --> 01:30:53,531
<i>Even Sarah found, one Christmas, that she
could no longer hear its sweet sound.</i>

802
01:30:53,698 --> 01:30:55,367
<i>Though I've grown old...</i>

803
01:30:55,533 --> 01:30:57,911
<i>...the bell still rings for me.</i>

804
01:30:58,078 --> 01:31:02,165
<i>As it does for all who truly believe.</i>

805
01:39:50,234 --> 01:39:52,236


